title: Gardens a home for Waifs
text:
Entertainment Waifs enjoy warm Cairns welcome by: What are these? GARDEN SEAT: Nello and Julie Terzi relax with their children Thomas, 9, and Farrah, 12, at Music Botanica at the gardens. PICTURE: ANNA ROGERS Source: News Corp Australia 
THE Waifs have received a warm welcome in Cairns, performing to a sold-out crowd at the Botanic Gardens yesterday. 
The Australian folk-rock outfit was supported by blues and roots musician Mia Dyson and local singer-songwriter Em Joy as part of the Tanks’ outdoor Music Botanica concert series. 
The Terzi family from Mareeba was one of many who lined the lawn, perched in camping chairs or sprawled on picnic rugs. 
“It was great, the gardens were full,” said dad Nello Terzi. 
“I’ve been a fan of The Waifs for some years now. 
“One of the girls brought their son on to the stage and everyone got up and danced and enjoyed the day.” 
The Waifs are on a national tour after releasing their LP titled Beautiful You .
